The paper deals with computational problems related to voting systems and social choice theory, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational social choice (cs.GT). The use of algorithms and parameterized complexity also suggests a connection to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper may also be relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC) due to its focus on fixed-parameter tractability.
